<%# Phase 26 — 01d. Layout-level webhook help modal.

    The Slack + Discord pane `[help]` links open this modal instead of
    navigating. The dialog hosts a Turbo Frame
    (`webhook_help_modal_frame`); the Stimulus `webhook-help-modal`
    controller (mounted on `<body>`) sets the frame's `src` to
    `/settings/webhooks/help/<provider>` on open. The controller's
    `show` action renders the Markdown-rendered guide inside a
    matching `<turbo-frame>` so Turbo swaps in the content.

    Closing semantics mirror the project's other layout-level modals
    (notifications, search, IGDB search):
      - Esc — native <dialog> Escape handling + an explicit keydown
        guard on the controller.
      - Backdrop click — `clickOutside` action.
      - `[close]` bracketed link — `close` action.

    No JS `confirm()` / `alert()` / `prompt()` and no
    `data-turbo-confirm` (CLAUDE.md hard rule). %>
<%# The help modal is wider than the other dialog variants because it
    hosts multi-paragraph prose, code blocks, and tables (Troubleshooting).
    `pane-dialog` clamps to 600px, `confirm-modal` to 420px — neither is
    enough room for the rendered guide without horizontal scroll. We set
    width inline so the modal stays self-contained and we don't have to
    introduce another class variant.

    `overflow-x: hidden` + `overflow-wrap: anywhere` on the inner content
    keeps long webhook-URL strings from blowing the layout out
    horizontally; they wrap inside the code block instead. %>
<dialog id="webhook-help-modal"
        class="pane-dialog webhook-help-modal"
        style="max-width: 900px; width: min(900px, 92vw);"
        data-action="click->webhook-help-modal#clickOutside keydown->webhook-help-modal#keydown">
  <div style="padding: 12px 16px; max-height: 80vh; overflow-y: auto; overflow-x: hidden; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-wrap: break-word;">
    <%= turbo_frame_tag "webhook_help_modal_frame", src: nil, loading: "lazy" %>
    <div class="modal-footer">
      <%= render(BracketedLinkComponent.new(
            label: "close",
            href: "#",
            data: { action: "click->webhook-help-modal#close" }
          )) %>
    </div>
  </div>
</dialog>
